    "studentSupport": "Trinity College Dublin provides a comprehensive and student-focused support system to ensure that international students have a smooth, comfortable, and successful study abroad experience. For students planning to study abroad in Ireland, the university offers dedicated services that cover every stage of the journey—from pre-arrival guidance to on-campus support and career development.\n\nOne of the key services is the International Student Support Team, which assists students with visa guidance, immigration formalities, and pre-departure information. Upon arrival in Dublin, students are welcomed through comprehensive orientation programs that introduce them to campus facilities, academic systems, and life in Ireland.\n\nThe university also offers strong academic support services, including tutoring, writing assistance, and study workshops. Dedicated advisors are available to guide students through course selection, academic challenges, and career planning. For personal well-being, Trinity provides counselling services, health support, and mental wellness programs.\n\nAccommodation support is another important aspect, with assistance provided for both on-campus and off-campus housing. Trinity also offers a buddy and mentoring system, where new international students are paired with experienced students to help them adjust to the new environment, culture, and academic expectations.",

