    "studentSupport": "Northeastern University offers comprehensive and student-focused support services for international students, ensuring a smooth transition to academic and social life in the United States. The university is committed to providing a welcoming, inclusive, and supportive environment for students from all over the world.\n\nBefore arrival, Northeastern provides pre-departure guidance to help students prepare for their journey. This includes assistance with admission procedures, visa application guidance, accommodation options, and travel planning. Once students arrive on campus in Boston, they participate in orientation programs that introduce them to university resources, academic expectations, and campus life.\n\nThe university has a dedicated Office of Global Services (OGS) that supports international students with immigration-related matters, including visa regulations, maintaining legal status, and work authorization such as CPT and OPT. This ensures students can focus on their studies without administrative stress.\n\nFor academic success, Northeastern University provides a wide range of academic support services, including advising, tutoring, writing centers, and study workshops. Students can also interact with faculty members and advisors for personalized guidance.\n\nNortheastern places strong emphasis on career development and employability support. Through its career services and the well-known Co-op program, students gain access to internships, job placements, resume-building workshops, and interview preparation. This helps international students build strong professional profiles and secure global career opportunities.\n\nThe university also prioritizes student wellbeing and mental health, offering confidential counselling services, wellness programs, and health services. To encourage social integration, Northeastern organizes cultural events, networking sessions, and student engagement activities where international students can connect with peers from different backgrounds. With over 400 student organizations, students can easily find communities that match their interests and culture.",

    "hostelFacilities": "Northeastern University offers a range of on-campus and off-campus accommodation options to ensure international students enjoy a comfortable and convenient living experience in Boston. The university's urban campus features modern on-campus residences that are particularly recommended for first-year and incoming international students due to their proximity to lecture halls, libraries, and campus facilities.\n\nOn-campus residences include a mix of suite-style rooms, standard single and double rooms, and apartment-style housing. All residences are equipped with high-speed Wi-Fi, common areas, laundry facilities, communal kitchens, and 24-hour security.\n\nFor students who prefer off-campus living, Northeastern's off-campus housing services provide guidance on vetted private rentals and shared apartments across Boston. As Boston is a major city, students have access to a wide variety of housing options at varying price points, with proximity to public transit making commuting convenient.\n\nNortheastern's residential life and student support teams provide year-round assistance with accommodation queries and pastoral care, ensuring a safe, inclusive, and supportive living environment for all international students.",

    "studentLife": "Student life at Northeastern University is vibrant, diverse, and highly engaging, offering students a well-rounded experience that goes beyond academics. Located in Boston, the university provides a dynamic urban environment where students can enjoy both campus life and the opportunities of a global city.\n\nAt Northeastern, students are encouraged to actively participate in clubs, societies, and extracurricular activities. With over 400 student organizations, including cultural groups, technical clubs, entrepreneurship societies, and arts communities, students can explore their interests, develop leadership skills, and build strong social connections.\n\nOne of the most unique aspects of student life at Northeastern University is its Co-op (co-operative education) program, which allows students to alternate between academic study and full-time paid work experience. This not only strengthens practical knowledge but also helps students gain real-world exposure and build professional networks while still studying.\n\nThe university also promotes a healthy and active lifestyle through its excellent sports and recreational facilities, including modern gyms, fitness centers, and athletic fields. Students can participate in varsity sports, club sports, or recreational activities, helping them maintain physical fitness and reduce academic stress.\n\nCampus life includes various social spaces such as cafés, lounges, and student hubs, where students can relax, collaborate, and spend time with friends. Regular events, cultural festivals, workshops, and networking sessions are organized throughout the year.\n\nNortheastern University is also known for its multicultural and inclusive environment, with students from over 140 countries. This diversity allows students to gain global exposure, learn about different cultures, and build international friendships, which are valuable for future careers.",

    "recognition": "Northeastern University holds strong national and international recognition, cementing its status as one of the most respected private research universities in the United States. The university is regionally accredited by the New England Commission of Higher Education (NECHE), and its degrees are recognized by employers, academic institutions, and professional bodies across the globe.\n\nNortheastern is a member of key global academic networks and maintains extensive research partnerships with leading companies, government agencies, and institutions worldwide. The D'Amore-McKim School of Business holds AACSB accreditation, one of the most prestigious business school accreditations internationally. The College of Engineering programs are accredited by ABET, ensuring graduates meet the highest professional standards.\n\nThe university's Co-op program is internationally recognized as a gold standard in experiential education. Northeastern alumni hold leadership positions in top multinational companies, research institutions, and government organizations worldwide, giving graduates a strong competitive advantage in both Indian and international job markets.",

